&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work for one of the UK’s largest Trusts, situated in the heart of the “Garden of England”, just a stone’s throw from London and with easy, fast access to France and beyond?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have excellent full time opportunities across the following specialty: Urology, within Surgical Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Kent &amp; Canterbury Hospital in Canterbury&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people who have some previous experience of working in the specialty, but we also encourage applications from qualified nurses that have not worked specifically in Urology. We will support you to enable development of skills across patient pathways, and access to development opportunities with our excellent links with the University of Kent and Christchurch University College.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to provide safe and effective care that exceeds the expectations of our patients and the public and we are &lt;strong&gt;looking for excellent nurses who embrace our Trust values and care so that:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People feel &lt;strong&gt;cared&lt;/strong&gt; for as individuals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People feel &lt;strong&gt;safe&lt;/strong&gt;, reassured and involved&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People feel that we are &lt;strong&gt;making a difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People feel teamwork, trust and &lt;strong&gt;respect&lt;/strong&gt; sit at the heart of everything we do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about working with us, or to arrange an informal visit to see us in action, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kent &amp; Canterbury Hospital – Alexandra Tradd, Ward Manager. Tel: 01227 766877 ext: 722 2877. Email: alexandra.trad@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
